result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeffrey L. Jeter was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jeffrey L. Jeter in court with attorney Jessica L Schuster.  Defendant Jeffrey L. Jeter in custody.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 13CF112, 14CF10, 14CF129, 15CM72, and 15CF91 @ 10:25 a.m. Statement of negotiated plea filed. Counsel and Def agree. Court reviews agreement. on 15CF91 Def will plead to cts 1, 2 and 5, remaining counts to be dismissed and read in. 15CM72 Def will plead to charge. 15CM91 - waiver of prelim filed. Court reviews, finds Def understands, accepts waiver and finds probable cause and binds over. Information filed. Copy received, reading waived. 15CM72 ct 1 - charge/penalties reviewed. Guilty plea. 15CF91 ct 1 - charge/penalties reviewed. Guilty plea. Ct 2 - charge/penalties reviewed. Guilty plea. Ct 5 - charge/penalties reviewed. Guilty plea. Court reviews plea quest. and constitutional rights. Court explains felony conviction voting and firearms restrictions. Victim rights complied. Atty Schuster satisfied. Court finds Def understands. Stip factual basis. Court finds guilty of 15CM72 and cts 1, 2, 5 in 15CF91. Cts 3, 4, 6 & 7 dismissed consistent with agreement. Parties recommend following written agreement.
13CF112, 14CF10, 14CF129 - no corrections to revocation summary. Court reviews agreement. State asks on 14CF129 that $500 restitution be paid as part of ext. supv. No objection. Def makes statement. Court gives remarks, approves joint recommendation. 
15CF91 ct 1 - 5 yrs prison, 2 yrs initial, 3 yrs ext supv, conditions include restitution tbd w/in 60 days or set for hrg, costs.
Ct 2 - 1 yr jail concurrent to ct 1, costs. Ct 5 - 5 yrs prison, 2 yrs initial, 3 yrs ext supv, conditions include, restitution tbd w/in 60 days or set for hrg.  No credit.
15CM72 ct 1 - 1 yr jail, concurrent, costs. No sentence credit.
14CF129 ct 1  5 yrs prison, 2 yrs initial, 3 yrs ext supv, ct 2 - 3 yrs prison, 1  yr init, 2 yrs ext supv, concurrent, $500 restitution, 177 days credit. Other obl civil judgment.
14CF10  ct 1 - 3 yrs prison, 1 yr init, 2 yrs ext supv, ct 2 - 9 months jail, concurrent to ct 1 and to others. Civil judgment for fin. obl. 43 days sent credit.
13CF112 ct 2 90 days jail, 30 days sent credit. Civil judgment for court obligations.
Earned release/subst. abuse and challenge inc. programs. Postconviction rights. Back on record - Court clarifies all cases concurrent to all. 15CF91 is controlling case.
Sentencing hearing on revocation at 06-11-2015 11:00 am

Defendant Jeffrey L. Jeter in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Defendant Jeffrey L. Jeter in custody.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 14CF115 and 14CF129 @ 10:55 a.m. Court also calls 14CF10 and 13CF112. Agreement stated - 13CF112 ct 1 dismiss and read in, ct 2 withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, AODA follow through, anger management, counseling as recommended, costs. 14CF10 - plea to both cts, withheld sentence, 2 yrs probation, AODA and follow through, costs, other counseling deemed appropriate. 14CF115 - dimsiss and read in. 14CF129 plea to cts 1 & 2 , ct 1 withheld sentence, 2 yrs probation, AODA follow through, restitution $500 joint & several, counsel deemed appropriate, costs. Ct 2 withheld sentence, 2 yrs probation, counseling deemed appropriate, costs, restitution $500 joint & several, State will argue 9 months jail, however, stipulate to 120 days jail, credit only if revoked.   14CF10 and 14CF129 - state agrees to reserve right to expunge under 973.015 as long as no crimes to probable cause and all financail obligations paid. Atty Laufenberg and Def agree. 13CF112 ct 2 - Def admits prior convictions. No contest plea. Ct 1 dismissed consistent with agreement. 14CF10 ct 1 - no contest plea, ct 2 - no contest. 14CF129 - Court reviews prelim rights, finds Def understands and waiver freely made. Probable cause found. Information filed, copy received. Plea to ct 1 - no contest. Plea to ct 2 - no contest. Ct 3 dismissed consistent with agreement. 14CF115 - Dismissed consistent with agreement. Court reviews plea quest. and constitutional rights. Atty Laufenberg satisfied/factual basis. Court finds Def understands, accepts pleas and finds guilty of 13CF112 ct 2 disorderly conduct as repeater;  guilty of 14CF10 ct 1 felony bail jumping and ct 2 resisting or obstructing as repeater; guilty of 14CF129 ct 1 burglary, and ct 2 felony bail jumping.  Statement by Atty Laufenberg. Def makes statement. Remarks by the Court, accepts agreement.
13CF112 ct 2 - sentence withheld, 1 yr probation, AODA and follow through, anger managment, counseling deemed appropriate, costs including DNA surcharge.
14CF10 ct 1 - sentence withheld, 2 yrs probation, AODA and follow through, other counseling, costs including DNA surcharge. DNA sample. Def advised of voting and firearms rights.  Ct 2 - sentence withheld, 2 yrs probation, same conditions as ct 1. Court reserves right to expunge upon successful completion of probation, no crimes to probable cause and all financial obligations paid. 
14CF129 ct 1 - sentence withheld, 2 yrs probation, concurrent to 14CF10 and 13CF112. AODA and follow through, counseling, costs, restitution $500 joint & several. Ct 2 - sentence withheld, 2 yrs probation, 120 days jail, when Def gets medical appt, may request Court to grant furlough for appointment or for job interview. Huber if/when employed, counseling, costs including DNA surcharge, restitution $500. Reserve right to expunge if successfully completes probation. Recall 7/18/16 @ 1:00 p.m.  Credit if revoked - 13CF112 - 1 day credit, 14CF10 - 14 days, 14CF129 - 28 days.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. 14CF10 - return bond to poster. Postconviction rights. (Confirmed with the Court - all probation concurrent.)

Defendant Jeffrey L. Jeter in court with attorney Wright C Laufenberg.  Ralph M Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 13CF112 & 14CF10 @ 10:52 am.  Atty Laufenberg gives statement.  Status conference scheduled for August 13, 2014 at 09:15 am.

Defendant Jeffrey L. Jeter in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Ralph M Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 13CF112 & 14CF10 @ 10:08 am.  Atty Laufenberg waives p.h.   Defendant waives right to preliminary hearing on both cases.  Court accepts waiver and finds probable cause on both cases. Information Filed on both cases. Atty Laufenberg has copy of informations, waives reading, reserve rights & enters not guilty pleas. Court enters not guilty pleas on 13CF112 & 14CF10. Bond remains.  Status conference scheduled for April 11, 2014 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Jeffrey L. Jeter in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Ralph M Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint received, waive reading.  Time limits waived for preliminary.  Case to track 13CF112  Preliminary requested.  Bond will continue  Preliminary hearing scheduled for February 18, 2014 at 10:00 am.
